# Refactor Customers Section

The "Customers" section in the Admin Dashboard currently displays placeholder data. This plan outlines the steps to implement a real backend endpoint for fetching users and connecting it to the frontend.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [NEW] [server/routes/users.js](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/server/routes/users.js)
- Create a new route file for user management.
- Implement `GET /` endpoint to fetch all users (excluding sensitive data like passwords).
- Protect the route with `auth` and `adminAuth` middleware.

#### [MODIFY] [server/index.js](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/server/index.js)
- Register the new `/api/users` route.

### Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx)
- Add state to [AdminDashboard](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx#1303-1536) to store users.
- Fetch users in the `useEffect` hook alongside products and orders.
- Update [AdminCustomers](file:///c:/Users/Adonis/Downloads/App/src/pages/AdminDashboard.tsx#311-338) component to accept `users` prop and map over real data.
- Remove hardcoded placeholder loop.

